Build CRM Analytics Dashboards

Create a CRM Analytics dashboard with a Template

Dashboard templates speed your analytics development by automatically creating dashboards. Some provide blank layouts that you populate with data, while other “smart” templates create dashboards that require little to no additional configuration.

To create a dashboard: 
Create and Edit Analytics Dashboards

Each dashboard template provides a prebuilt layout with empty widgets, sections, and a color scheme. Use the widget wizards to populate the widgets with your data. Choose the blank template if you prefer to create your own layout.

Choose smart templates to create complete dashboards already populated with your data. They also include a configuration wizard to guide you through the creation process.

From the home page, select Create | Dashboard.
Choose Blank Dashboard or Dashboard from Template, and click Create.
If you use a smart template, follow the instructions in the wizard.
If you use a traditional template, add a query to each widget by clicking the icon inside the empty widget.

To set the dashboard properties, click  and then click Dashboard Properties.
The permissions on the app determine each user’s access to the dashboard.

Create and Manage Dashboards with Reusable Components

Dashboard Properties
These properties apply to a dashboard designer dashboard. Some of them are the default widget properties that you can apply to each widget to ensure a consistent appearance.

Smart Dashboards
Use a smart dashboard template to create a ready-made dashboard that’s prepopulated with your Salesforce data.
